				FAQs			












Find answers to our frequently asked questions below. If you can’t find an answer to your question, please contact us.



Can I submit my book to Greenfields Press for publication?



Greenfields Press is currently only accepting submissions during open call-out windows that fit our specific criteria. Please visit our Submissions page for details of open call-outs as well as general guidelines for submitting.



How do I apply for a job or work experience at Greenfields Press?



Greenfields Press is not currently advertising any new job roles. Please keep an eye on our website and social media channels for announcements about new opportunities.



Does Greenfields Press publish ebooks?



Yes — all of our titles are available as ebooks, and can be purchased directly from our website. Each book is delivered as a high-quality digital file immediately after purchase.



How can I request a review copy of a book?



If you work in the media or have a blog and would like to request a review copy, please contact us with details of your publication or platform. We are also keen to hear from online influencers and reviewers with an interest in professional development, leadership, and working life.



How can I request permission to use an extract from a Greenfields Press book?



Greenfields Press controls and asserts intellectual property rights for all writers it publishes according to international copyright law. This establishes the right of the author to be recognised as the creator of the work and supports their economic right to receive fair reward for use of that work by others. To make a permissions request please contact us.



How can I find out if rights are available for a particular book?



Please contact us to enquire about translation or other rights for our books.





















