				Submissions			












Greenfields Press publishes books for professionals navigating every stage of their working life. Our Path Series explores the real, unspoken challenges of freelancing, leadership, coaching, executive life, and retirement — books written with honesty, craft, and care.



We are seeking to grow our catalogue by publishing writers and books that speak to a broad professional readership. Read on for general advice about submitting to us, as well as details of any open call-outs.



General Advice



All writers are welcome to submit book ideas which fit our call-outs, including emerging writers, those we’ve published before, and those published elsewhere. We’re also keen to hear from those who may not consider themselves a writer but have a compelling idea and the ability to bring it to life.



We want to publish books that reflect a full spectrum of professional lived experience. The more diverse the perspectives we publish, the stronger and more meaningful our books will be. We encourage submissions from all communities, faiths, backgrounds, ages, and identities.



Details of any open submission call-outs will be listed below. We will always make commissioning decisions based on our editorial priorities and what readers want. We will not accept submissions outside of call-out windows or which do not fit what we are looking for.



We respect the intellectual property of all ideas submitted to us and will never act upon or share these outside the submission process.



Please note that we only publish books suitable for an adult audience.



All submissions received during open submission windows will be acknowledged and we will notify writers of the outcome of their submission. Due to the size of our team, if unsuccessful, we may be unable to correspond further about the outcome of individual submissions.



Book ideas selected for development are subject to additional commissioning processes. Book publication is not agreed until writers are contracted. Terms within all issued contracts apply.



We cannot accept simultaneous submissions or pursue book ideas which are in development elsewhere. You must notify us if you submit your idea to other publishers so we can withdraw it from our commissioning process.



We cannot accept paper submissions — any posted submissions received will not be considered or acknowledged.



We can only consider the work of writers who are aged eighteen or over at the time of submission.



We will not accept any submissions which contain work generated in part or entirely by AI programmes.





















